tical prediction of k^{-2/3} for incompressible flows.\nFinally, the comparison with incompressible results showed that the scalar in\ncompressible turbulence with Sc=1 lacked a conspicuous bump structure in its\nspectrum, but was more intermittent in the dissipative range.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 17 May 2015 17:34:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
